ork as part of their own limited company in an arrangement where the &lsquo;employer&rsquo; is actually a customer or client</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Employment rights</h2>\n\n<p>Workers are entitled to certain employment rights, including:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>getting the <a href=\"/your-right-to-minimum-wage\" title=\"Your right to the minimum wage\">National Minimum Wage</a></li>\n  <li>protection against unlawful deductions from wages</li>\n  <li>the statutory minimum level of paid <a href=\"/holiday-entitlement-rights\" title=\"Holiday entitlement\">holiday</a></li>\n  <li>the statutory minimum length of rest breaks</li>\n  <li>not to work more than <a href=\"/maximum-weekly-working-hours\" title=\"Maximum weekly working hours\">48 hours on average per week</a> or to opt out of this right if they choose</li>\n  <li>protection against unlawful <a href=\"/discrimination-your-rights\" title=\"Discrimination\">discrimination</a></li>\n  <li>protection for <a href=\"/whistleblowing\" title=\"Whistleblowing\">&lsquo;whistleblowing&rsquo;</a> (reporting wrongdoing in the workplace)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>They may also be entitled to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/statutory-maternity-pay\" title=\"Statutory Maternity Pay\">Statutory Maternity Pay</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/paternity-leave-pay-employees\" title=\"Ordinary Statutory Paternity Pay\">Ordinary Statutory Paternity Pay</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/statutory-sick-pay-ssp\" title=\"Statutory Sick Pay\">Statutory Sick Pay</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p><a href=\"/agency-workers-your-rights/overview\" title=\"Agency workers: your rights\">Agency workers</a> have specific rights from the first day at work.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Workers usually aren&rsquo;t entitled to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>minimum notice periods if their employment will be ending (eg if an employer is dismissing them)</li>\n  <li>protection against <a href=\"/dismissal/unfair-and-constructive-dismissal\" title=\"Unfair dismissal\