p>Employers must also ensure that fixed-term employees get:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the same pay and conditions as permanent staff</li>\n  <li>the same or equivalent benefits package</li>\n  <li>information about permanent vacancies in the organisation</li>\n  <li>protection against redundancy or <a href=\"/dismissal\" title=\"Dismissals\">dismissal</a> </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>However, they&rsquo;re only entitled to the same rights as permanent staff working for the same employer, and not an associated employer&rsquo;s organisation.</p>\n\n<p>Anyone who&rsquo;s worked continually for the same employer for 2 years or more has the same <a href=\"/redundant-your-rights\" title=\"Redundancy\">redundancy rights</a> as a permanent employee.</p>\n\n<h2>Workplace disputes</h2>\n<p>Workers on fixed-term contracts should try to sort out any concerns they have with their manager.</p>\n\n<p>If they&rsquo;re still not satisfied, they can ask their employer for a written statement explaining their treatment, or complain using the employer&rsquo;s <a href=\"/solve-workplace-dispute\" title=\"Solve a workplace dispute\">grievance procedure</a>.</p>\n\n<p>Their final option is to make a claim to an <a href=\"/employment-tribunals\" title=\"Employment tribunal\">employment tribunal</a>.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/fixed-term-contracts/renewing-or-ending-a-fixedterm-contract","slug":"renewing-or-ending-a-fixedterm-contract","order":3,"title":"Renewing or ending a fixed-term contract","body":"<h2>Ending a fixed-term contact</h2>\n<p>Fixed-term contracts will normally end automatically when they reach the agreed end date. The employer doesn&rsquo;t have to give any notice.</p>\n\n<h2>If a contract isn&rsquo;t renewed</h2>\n\n<p>This is considered to be a dismissal, and the employer needs to show that there&rsquo;s a &lsquo;fair&rsquo; reason for not renewing the contract (eg, if they were planning to stop doing the work the contract was for).</p>\n\n<p>Workers have the right:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>not to be unfairly dismissed after 2 years&rsquo; service (for employees who were in employment before 6 April 2012, it&rsquo;s 1 year&rsquo;s service)  </li>\n  <li>to a written statement of reasons for not renewing the contract (after 1 year’s service)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>They may be entitled to statutory redundancy payments after 2 years&rsquo; service if the work ends unexpectedly.</p>\n\n<h2>If the employer wants to end the contract earlier</h2>\n\n<p>What happens depends on the terms of the contract. If:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>it says nothing about being ended early, the employer may be in breach of contract</li>\n  <li>it says it can be ended early, and the employer has given proper notice, the contract can be ended</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The minimum notice period fixed-term employees are entitled to is:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>after 1 month’s continuous service, but less than 2 years &ndash; 1 week</li>\n  <li>after 2 years&rsquo; continuous employment &ndash; 1 week for each year worked </li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>These are the minimum periods, and the contract may specify a longer notice period.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>If an employer ends a contract without giving the proper notice, the employee may be able to claim breach of contract.</p>\n\n<h2>Working longer than the contract&rsquo;s end date</h2>\n\n<p>If an employee continues working past the end of a contract without it being formally renewed, there&rsquo;s an &lsquo;implied agreement&rsquo; by the employer that the end date has changed.</p>\n\n<p>The employer still needs to be give proper notice if they want to dismiss the worker.</p>\n\n<div class=\"example\">\n<p><strong>Example</strong><br />\nIf a contract was for 1 month but the employee actually worked for 3 months, they&rsquo;d still be entitled to the minimum notice period (1 week).</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>The limit on renewing a fixed-term contract</h2>\n\n<p>Any employee on a fixed-term contract for 4 or more years will automatically become a permanent employee when their contract is renewed or they are given a new contract.</p>\n\n<p>However, an employer and unions (or a staff association) may make a collective agreement that removes the automatic right to become a permanent employee in these circumstances.</p>\n\n<h2>Renewing a fixed-term contract on less favourable terms</h2>\n\n<p>If an employer wants to do this, the employee can negotiate with them to reach an agreement. </p>\n\n<p>If the contract ends and they have been unable to reach an agreement, the employee may be able to claim <a href=\"/dismissal\" title=\"Dismissal\">unfair dismissal</a>.</p>\n\n<h2>Ending the contract early</h2>\n\n<p>Employees must <a href=\"/handing-in-your-notice-resigning-leaving-job\" title=\"Handing in your notice\">hand in their notice</a> 1 week in advance if they&rsquo;ve worked for an employer for a month or more. The contract may state that they need to give more notice.</p>\n"}]},"tags":[{"title":"Contracts of employment and working hours","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people%2Fcontracts.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes types of worker, employee rights, overtime and changes to contracts","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people%2Fcontracts","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people/contracts"},"parent":{"title":"Employing people","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes pay, contracts and hiring","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people"},"parent":null}},{"title":"Your contract and working hours","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working%2Fcontract-working-hours.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes employment status, workers' right