"title":"Compulsory overtime","body":"<h2>Can an employee be forced to work overtime?</h2>\n<p>Employees only have to work overtime if their contract says so. </p>\n\n<p>Even if it does, by law, they can&rsquo;t usually be forced to work more than an average of <a href=\"/maximum-weekly-working-hours\" title=\"Maximum weekly working hours\">48 hours per week</a>. An employee can agree to work longer - but this agreement must be in writing and signed by them.</p>\n\n<h2>Can an employee be stopped from working overtime?</h2>\n<p>Unless an employee&rsquo;s contract guarantees them overtime, their employer can stop them from working it. </p>\n\n<p>However, their employer can&rsquo;t <a href=\"/discrimination-your-rights/discrimination-at-work\" title=\"Discrimination at work\">discriminate against anyone</a>, eg by stopping some employees from working overtime while letting others do so.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/overtime-your-rights/parttime-workers","slug":"parttime-workers","order":3,"title":"Part-time workers","body":"\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Usually, <a href=\"/part-time-worker-rights\" title=\"Part-time workers' rights\">part-time workers</a> mustn’t be treated less favourably than full-time staff.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Unless it says differently in a part-time worker&rsquo;s employment contract, their employer will usually only pay overtime if they work:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>longer hours than set out in the employment contract</li>\n  <li>more than the normal working hours of full-time staff and full-time staff would get extra pay for working these hours</li>\n  <li>unsocial hours (eg late at night) for which full-time staff would get more pay</li>\n</ul>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/overtime-your-rights/time-off-and-paid-leave","slug":"time-off-and-paid-leave","order":4,"title":"Time off and paid leave","body":"<h2>Time off in lieu (TOIL)</h2>\n<p>Some employers give their employees time off instead of paying for overtime. This is known as &lsquo;time off in lieu&rsquo;. </p>\n\n<p>The terms (eg when it can be taken) are agreed between employee and employer.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/overtime-your-rights/help-and-advice","slug":"help-and-advice","order":5,"title":"Help and advice","body":"<p>Employees can contact the Pay and Work Rights Helpline for free and confidential advice on working hours.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Pay and Work Rights Helpline</strong><br />\n<a href=\"https://payandworkrights.direct.gov.uk/\" title=\"Pay and Work Rights Helpline\" rel=\"external\">Online enquiry form</a>  <br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong>  0800 917 2368</p>\n</div>\n"}]},"tags":[{"title":"Contracts of employment and working hours","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people%2Fcontracts.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes types of worker, employee rights, overtime and changes to contracts","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people%2Fcontracts","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people/contracts"},"parent":{"title":"Employing people","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes pay, contracts and hiring","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people"},"parent":null}},{"title":"Your contract and working hours","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working%2Fcontract-working-hours.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes employment status, workers' rights and changes to contracts","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=working%2Fcontract-working-hours","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/working/contract-working-hours"},"parent":{"title":"Working, jobs and pensions"